						               													<description>This is the fourth game in a series using the 3CP Game Engine, which employs custom cards and a deck of standard playing cards. It's more &amp;quot;warlike&amp;quot; than the others in that it uses a familiar &amp;quot;battle line&amp;quot; format, with players competing for five &amp;quot;theaters of war&amp;quot; by playing cards on either side of them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During the game you&amp;rsquo;ll acquire Force cards representing Land, Air, Sea, and Production &amp;ndash; by playing 3-card poker hands from a hand of seven cards. (Hence, &amp;ldquo;3CP&amp;rdquo; in the game&amp;rsquo;s title.) Card management in the form of &amp;ldquo;what poker hand to play now and what to save for later&amp;rdquo; is an important factor toward winning the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Close attention to your (and your opponent's) needs and how the game is evolving are required before placing your Force cards; the decision can be tough. Your goal is to triumph in three of the five theaters of war -- or outpoint your opponent -- and achieve victory.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;FINAL CARDS AND RULES NOW AVAILABLE AT WWW.3CPGAMES.COM! (Update Required)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
